Increase the value of shift in you get blurry/dark images.
Decrease the value if you want to increase the detail of the image.

The shot captures her from just above the eyebrows to below the chin, filling the frame with her face. Her green eyes shimmer with intricate iris detail, reflecting soft window light. The lighting is natural and diffused, creating gentle shadows that define the contours of her cheekbones, nose, and jawline. # Qwen KSampler settings

## Steps
Even if the official page suggest to use 50 steps, you can reach good results even with just 10 steps.  I suggest to stay around 25-30 steps.

## CFG
If you want to speed up the workflow, do not use negative prompts and set the CFG to 1.0.  Default is at 4.0, I use 2.5-3.0.

## Sampler - Scheduler
I suggest to use dpmpp_2m + sgm_uniform, but you can play with settings here!

# WAN 2.2 Ksampler settings

## Steps
I suggest to keep it at 40-50 steps for better quality.


## Sampler - Scheduler
Best combo here is res_2s + bong_tangent.   
Install [RES4LYF](https://github.com/ClownsharkBatwing/RES4LYF) custom node!

## Denoise
Keep it around 0.25-0.30 for better results and to keep better consistency with the Qwen Image output.

nodes.title: Workflow quick guide
widgets_values:
# Workflow quick guide

## Models
You will need the Qwan Image model and the GGUF of Wan 2.2 t2v Low Noise model, as with the standard one you will get OOM errors.   
The first will generate the base image, having better prompt adherence and great detailed output.  The second will add realistic details to people skin, eyes and hair.
1. [Qwen Image model](https://docs.comfy.org/tutorials/image/qwen/qwen-image#1-workflow-file)
2. [Wan 2.2 t2v low noise model Q8 GGUF](https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-GGUF/resolve/main/LowNoise/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-LowNoise-Q8_0.gguf?download=true) or choose any other quantization [here](https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-GGUF/tree/main/LowNoise)

## The workflow
Qwen model is extremely good at following your prompt, but it lacks details and quality for photo realistic images.  This is why I added a second pass with Wan 2.2 t2v model, a facedetailer module and an upscale module that uses the 2nd pass model and [UltraSharpV2](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensors?download=true) as upscale model.  Negative prompt can be used, but remember to set CFG to a value higer than 1.00.   
You can choose to apply or bypass the Facedetailer module, the Upscaler module and the Save Image module.

Use key "1" and "2" to navigate the Workflow.
